e the student carefully through this complex debate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aIslamic Studies. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aAbdel-Malek, Anouar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAhmad, Aijaz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDallmayr, Fred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoucault, Michel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGabrieli, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGramsci, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHegel, G. W . F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInden, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKing, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKopf, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLittle, Donald P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLowe, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacKenzie, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartino, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarx, Karl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMelman, Billie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMill, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoore-Gilbert, B. J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNietzsche, Friedrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPollock, Shel